[start section id="20112"]

I explained to Mr. Buck and his wife carefully that it is a common recommendation to tell patients to continue with chemotherapy after receiving neoadjuvant chemotherapy and radiation therapy.  It is our practice to recommend FOLFOX, but this is not based on the clinical trial but just in our day-to-day practice.  Unfortunately, we do not have a prospective randomized clinical trial that clearly defines if there is a role for FOLFOX or not after surgery.  He is young and otherwise very healthy so I think that it is reasonable to go back to an oxaliplatin-based regimen for four months, and he is agreeable.
We will start chemotherapy as soon as he has recovered from this, and then see him back two-weeks later.  I recommended to the patient not use masking tape and to consult the ostomy nurses.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

[end section id="20112"]

